  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nA clear and concise description of what the bug is.\r\n\r\n`make submodules` doesn't recurse as expected.\r\n\r\nThe `Makefile` has:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    git submodule init; \\\r\n    git submodule update --recursive; \\\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich doesn't recurse because the submodules are not `init`ed yet.\r\n\r\nThis causes the build to fail with:\r\n\r\n```\r\n       Failed to resolve file: \"/root/optimism/packages/contracts-bedrock/lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/test.sol\": No such file or directory (os error 2).\r\n        Check configured remappings..\r\n           --> \"/root/optimism/packages/contracts-bedrock/lib/forge-std/src/Test.sol\"\r\n               \"ds-test/test.sol\"\r\n        ELIFECYCLE  Command failed with exit code 1.\r\n```\r\n\r\n`git submodule update --init --recursive` both `init`s and updates the submodules recursively, as expected.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n\r\n`make devnet-up`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\ndevnet is up.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nIf applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: macOS 14.1.0\r\n - Package Version (or commit hash): `develop`\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\r\nReported by @jcstein\r\n\r\n",
